general example where the vertices are of the form (1-u)Ei + u(-Ej) = Ei\
-u(Ei+Ej) with u going from 0 to 1.  All of these vertices have the sum of\
the coordinates equal to 1 - 2u, so we go from D+ to D- as u goes from 0\
to 1.\
